Jaguar Seeks Government Help for Engine Plant, Telegraph Says

-- B y   S i m o n   C l a r k
-- 
2011-05-08T15:38:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-08/jaguar-seeks-government-help-for-engine-plant-telegraph-says.html
Jaguar  Land Rover  managers have met
U.K. government officials to seek financial support for a new
750 million-pound ($1.23 billion) engine plant, the Sunday
Telegraph  reported .  Three potential sites have been identified, with two in the
U.K. and the other in  India , according to the report.
Wolverhampton in the U.K. may be the most favored site, the
newspaper said. Jaguar Land Rover is the luxury-car unit of
